‚úÖ Introduction to JavaScript

JavaScript is a programming language used to create interactive and dynamic behavior on websites. It runs in the browser (like Chrome or Firefox) and can:

1. Respond to user actions (clicks, input)
2. Modify HTML/CSS content dynamically
3.Validate forms
4. Work with APIs and store data

It‚Äôs one of the core technologies of the web, along with HTML and CSS.

  üõ†Ô∏è Setting Up JavaScript (No Software Needed!)

You can write JavaScript in two easy ways:

1. Inline in HTML

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
  <head>
    <title>JS Example</title>
  </head>
  <body>
    <h1>Hello from JavaScript!</h1>

    <script>
      alert("Welcome to JavaScript!");
    </script>
  </body>
</html>


2. External File

Create a file named script.js and link it:

<script src="script.js"></script>

